Sure! Here's a simple JavaScript function that does exactly that:

```javascript
function sumEvenNumbers(arr) {
    let sum = 0;
    for (let num of arr) {
        if (num % 2 === 0) {
            sum += num;
        }
    }
    return sum;
}
```

You can use this function by passing an array of integers to it, and it will return the sum of all the even numbers in that array. For example:

```javascript
console.log(sumEvenNumbers([1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6])); // Output: 12 (2 + 4 + 6)
```

This function iterates through each number in the array, checks if it is even (using the modulus operator `%` to see if the remainder when divided by 2 is 0), and if it is, adds it to a running sum. Finally, it returns the sum of all even numbers found in the array.
